commit_list.message:
Add `allowDuplicateProperties` parsing option, and make it the default.

While discouraged, the JSON spec does allow the same property to be
present more than once in an object. The built-in node.js JSON parser
allows them, but json-bignum previously did not. This option (default
true, changing the previous behavior) makes json-bignum behave the
same way as JSON in this respect.

For example, consider the following JSON string:

`{"hello": "world1", "hello": "world2"}`

With `allowDuplicateProperties == false`, parsing above will throw a
SyntaxError. When `true` (new default), it will return:

`{"hello": "world2"}`

commit_list.message:
Better handling of internal errors.

1. Attempt to report internal errors as exceptions to Rollbar. Internal errors are reported in the normally-configured project (for examination by the project developers) and flagged as internal (for examination by Rollbar staff).
2. if reporting the internal error fails, send a mostly-static failsafe response. The failsafe is also reported in the project context, and flagged as both "internal" and "failsafe".
3. if the failsafe fails, log an error.

Additionally: all logger calls in lib/rollbar.rb are now done via wrappers (`log_error`, etc.) that catch exceptions in such calls.
